<p>write a paragraph here </p> 
<em> makes the test italicises. it is different from the <i> as it makes the texts between the tags stressed. while the i tag only styles the text as italics
similarly use <strong> instead of <b> i.e. bold. 
On code pen if you enter ! + tab then you get the boiler plate code. boiler plate code is a basic template.
..........................................................................................................................
<!DOCTYPE html> - tells the browser to render this code as an html 5 file
<html lang="en"> - tells the browser to consider everything between this and closing tag as an html file. 
<head> - holds informnation about the web page. 
  <meta charset="UTF-8"> -gives meta data of the document to the browser. utf-8 is the standard encoding. 
  <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Document</title> - tells the title to the browser 
</head>
<body>
  
</body>
</html>
